@300 =~Death Knight Kit, by Drizzt1180~
@301 =~death knight~
@302 =~Death Knight~
@303 =~DEATH KNIGHT: A Death Knight is created when a fallen paladin dies. This is a very rare occurrence of resurrection. When this happens the newly risen Death Knight will become evil with many evil related abilities. Instead of being half-fighter and half-cleric like a paladin, they become half-fighter and half-necromancer instead. They gain necromancy spells as innate abilities in place of their regular priest spells.

Advantages:
- May cast Larloch's Minor Drain as an innate ability. Gains one use at level 9 and an additional use at level 14.
- May cast Ghoul Touch as an innate ability. Gains one use at level 11 and an additional use at level 16.
- May cast Vampiric Touch as an innate ability. Gains one use at level 13 and an additional use at levels 16 and 17. 
- May cast Animate Dead as an innate ability. Gains one use at level 19. 
- May use Harm Touch ability. Gains one use at level 1. Harm Touch is a direct damage ability and will do 2d10 points of damage +1 point per level up to a maximum of 2d10+20 with a successful to-hit roll.
- May use Ebony Hand ability. Gains one use at level 10. The spell adds +1 THAC0 plus an additional +1 THAC0 for every three levels of the caster up to a maximum of +7. The spell lasts for 3 rounds plus 1 round/level up to a maximum of 24 rounds. 
- May use Kiss of Torment ability. Gains one use at level 15. With a successful to-hit roll, does 4d6 points of damage and stuns target for four rounds. A successful save will reduce the stun effect to two rounds. 
- May use Heart Blight ability. Gains one use at level 19. Will slay the target unless a save vs. death is made; with a successful save the target is still stunned for three rounds and suffers a -2 Dexterity penalty for ten rounds. Additionally the target must make another save vs. Death at -1 or lose 25% of their Hit Points and yet another save vs. Death at -2 or suffer another 18 damage. 

Disadvantages:
- May not gain the Paladin abilities
- May not exceed Specialization (two slots) in any weapon.
- Alignment restricted to evil.~

@310 =~Ebony Hand~
