@400 =~Wushi Ninja Kit, by Drizzt1180~
@401 =~wushi ninja~
@402 =~Wushi Ninja~
@403 =~WUSHI NINJA: The Wushi Ninjas are an evolved version of the regular ninjas. This happened along time ago, when ninjas were greatly exposed to magic. After time they began to gain the ability to cast spells. Like regular ninjas they have the ability to specialize in all weapons that a regular thief can use. They also are stronger than a regular thief, but cannot be as charming. The first Wushi Ninja was Nagura Firo.

Advantages:
- May cast Magic Missile as an innate ability. Gains one use at level 3 and an additional use at levels 9 and 18.
- May cast Cure Light Wounds as an innate ability. Gains one use at level 4 and an additional use at levels 10 and 19.
- May cast Shocking Grasp ability as an innate ability. Gains one use at level 5 and an additional use at levels 11 and 20.
- May cast Aganazzar's Scorcher as an innate ability. Gains one use at level 6 and an additional use at level 12.
- May cast Mirror Image as an innate ability. Gains one use at level 7 and an additional use at level 13.
- May cast Blur as an innate ability. Gains one use at level 14.
- May cast Minor Spell Turning as an innate ability. Gains one use at level 15.
- May cast Shadow Door as an innate ability. Gains one use at level 16.
- May cast Breach as an innate ability. Gains one use at level 17.
- In early levels, THAC0 is lower then a regular thief's progression but matches in later levels. 
- May Specialize (two slots) in any weapon available to Thieves.
- Gains a +1 bonus to Strength and Intelligence.

Disadvantages:
- Incurs a -2 penalty to Charisma.
- May not wear armor heavier than studded leather.
- Race restricted to human.
- May only distribute 20 skill points per level among thieving skills.~

@410 =~THAC0 Adjustment~

